Package org.oucs.gaboto.beans Description

GabotoBeans are simple objects following the convention of Java Beans (see the wikipedia article). They represent complex properties for GabotoEntity that cannot be represented using binary relationships (or in other words, need blank nodes and more than one rdf triple to be represented in the RDF Graph).

An example for such a complex property would be the address of a building. As an example of how addresses could be stored in RDF, see the RDF Primer.
